The paper deals with the application of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) to the problem of detecting surgical site infections in patients by analyzing time series of their blood sample measurements. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories, which are concerned with the development and application of algorithms that can learn from data and make intelligent decisions. The use of RNNs also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category, which focuses on the study of artificial neural networks and their applications. Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the computer vision (cs.CV) and computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories, which deal with the analysis of visual and textual data, respectively, and may be relevant to the analysis of blood sample measurements.
